external_knowledge:
- Cumulative case count refers to the total number of cancer cases for each patient, ordered by patient ID, tumor stage, and tumor grade; 
- Tumor stages (I, II, III, IV) indicate the progression of cancer, with I being the least severe and IV the most severe;
- Tumor grades (low, intermediate, high) reflect the aggressiveness of cancer cells.

